![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/47d9c6de-12d1-43a3-96a4-6a09328d92d5/1000080112.jpg?format=original)

In a major development for Marvel fans, Marvel Studios has officially greenlit a third season of the highly anticipated series, Daredevil: Born Again. The news, confirmed by Marvel's head of streaming Brad Winderbaum to IGN, puts to rest speculation about the show's future after it underwent a significant creative retooling.

Filming for Season 3 is set to begin in 2026. This confirmation is a huge relief for fans who have been following the show's complex journey since its announcement.

## The Retooling of Daredevil: Born Again

The series has been at the center of attention due to a dramatic creative overhaul that occurred during a production pause. Initially, the show was conceived as a legal procedural with a lighter tone and only a loose connection to the Netflix series. However, Marvel Studios decided to shift direction after reviewing early footage.

The studio hired a new creative team led by showrunner Dario Scardapane, a writer from the original The Punisher series. This retooling was a direct response to fan and internal feedback that the show needed to be more in line with the gritty, serialized tone of the beloved Netflix version.

The changes went beyond just the script. Original cast members from the Netflix series, including Deborah Ann Woll as Karen Page and Elden Henson as Foggy Nelson, were brought back to re-establish the core dynamic of the original show. Ayelet Zurer also returned as Vanessa Fisk, replacing a previously cast actress. These decisions signal that the new direction will serve as a direct and canonical continuation of the "Defenders Saga" on Disney+.

## What the Renewal Means for the Series

The upcoming Season 2, which is expected to premiere in early 2026, will be the first full season produced entirely under this retooled creative vision. For viewers, this means a more cohesive narrative and a closer connection to the characters and stories they have missed.

The greenlight for a third season shows that Marvel is confident in the new creative direction and is ready to invest in the long-term future of the series. With the return of key characters and a renewed focus on what made the original show a hit, Daredevil: Born Again is poised to reclaim its place as one of the most compelling superhero shows on television. The decision is a win for both the studio and the dedicated fanbase who have championed the character's return.